½ cup Marinara Sauce
6 unit Flour Tortillas
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
28 g Baby Spinach
132 g Mini Cucumber
86 g Cream Cheese
160 g Sweet Bell Pepper
1 tsp Garlic Salt
2 unit Gala Apple

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.

Cut cucumbers into quarters lengthwise. Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices. Core, then cut apples into 1/2-inch wedges.

Spread cream cheese over each tortilla. Spoon marinara sauce over top, then top with spinach and peppers. Sprinkle with cheese and half the garlic salt.

Tightly roll each tortilla over filling. Transfer assembled tortillas to a plate. Cover and microwave on high until cheese is melted, 1 min. Serve pizza wraps with cucumbers and apples on the side.